Introduction

GreatGuys was a three-member boy group under DNA Entertainment. Originally as nine, they debuted with nine members on August 25, 2017, with their first single "Last Men".

On August 23rd, 2022. it was announced that Jaei had left the group on August 23rd, 2022.

GreatGuys has announced that Haneul, Daun, Uiyeon, Dongin, and Hwalchan's contracts are ending and they are leaving the group. GreatGuys will continue with Horyeong, Donghwi, and Baekgyeol. Following the ending of their Japan concert which runs from January 21-29. After January 29 the members will be leaving and GreatGuys will continue with the remaining three members Horeyeon, Donghwi, and Baekgyeol.

On April 1, 2025, DNA Entertainment announced that all three members had left the company following the expiration of their contracts.
